    <h2 class="text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary my-6">Use Cases and Examples</h2>
    <p class="text-white mb-6">
      Local SEO strategies are versatile and can be adapted to various business models and industries. The core principle is to connect with customers in a specific geographic area, whether you're a single storefront or a multi-location enterprise.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 p-6 rounded-xl mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-4">Real-World Geographic Targeting</h4>
          <ol class="text-white space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
            <li><strong>Service-Area Businesses:</strong> A plumbing company can target specific neighborhoods or suburbs, ensuring they appear in "plumber near me" searches for homeowners in their operational zones.</li>
            <li><strong>Multi-Location Retail:</strong> A coffee shop chain can create optimized location pages for each store, allowing them to capture foot traffic from searches like "coffee shop downtown."</li>
            <li><strong>Professional Services:</strong> A law firm can optimize its Google Business Profile for practice areas like "personal injury lawyer in [City]," attracting high-value local clients.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
