      <p class="text-lg text-white italic">"<a href="https://birdeye.com/blog/state-of-google-business-profiles/" class="text-primary hover:underline">48% of customer actions on Google Business Profile listings are website visits (BirdEye, 2024)</a>. This single free tool is often the largest driver of local traffic and conversions."</p>
      <cite class="text-primary text-sm">— Local Search Industry Research</cite>
    </blockquote>

    <p class="text-white mb-4">
      Key focus areas include:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li><strong>Citation Consistency:</strong> Ensuring your NAP (Name, Address, Phone) is identical across all online directories.</li>
        <li><strong>Review Management:</strong> Actively encouraging and responding to customer reviews to build trust.</li>
        <li><strong>Local Schema Markup:</strong> Adding structured data to your website to help search engines understand your location, hours, and services.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Business Profile Optimization:</strong> Regularly updating your GBP with posts, photos, and accurate information.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-orbitron font-bold text-primary mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
    <details class="group bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20 rounded-xl mb-4">
      <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-orbitron font-bold text-primary">How much do local SEO services cost?</h3>
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
